menu "breadboard: bb_power_tps546"

config BB_TPS546_OFF_SETTLE_MS
    int "OPERATION_OFF settle delay (ms)"
    range 1 100
    default 5
    help
        After writing OPERATION_OFF at the start of the TPS546 init/recover
        cycle, the driver waits this many milliseconds for the output rail
        to drain and the regulator latch state to stabilise before writing
        the new config program. 5 ms is sufficient for typical inductor/cap
        combinations; increase on boards with large output capacitance.

endmenu
